==English==
===Etymology===
{{D.}} ''koek'' meaning cake and ''sissen'' meaning to sizzle.
===Noun===
'''koeksister'''
#(South African). A traditional Malay [[confection]]: deep-fried twisted or plaited doughnut immediately dipped in syrup. 
===Reference===
Jean Bradford: A Dictionary of South African English. Oxford 1978.
